    "name": "Question 8 @ 2017/2018",
    "Question": {
      "content": "Three points in an electric field A, B, C lie in a line and have potentials of 8.0V, 4.0V and -2.0V respectively. A negative charge is placed at point B and released at rest. Which way will it move if it moves at all?",
      "type": "OBJ",
      "options": [
        "toward A",
        "toward B",
        "it will not move",
        "toward point C"
      ]
    },
    "Answer": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "toward point C"
    },
    "Explanation": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "A negative charge moves from a region of higher potential to lower potential. Since B is at 4.0V and C is at -2.0V, the negative charge will move toward C."
    },
